  "prompt": "Is GTA IV released on Android?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Grand Theft Auto IV (GTA IV)** has **not been officially released on Android**. Rockstar Games, the developer of the Grand Theft Auto series, has brought several titles to Android devices, including:\n\n- **Grand Theft Auto III**\n- **Grand Theft Auto: Vice City**\n- **Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas**\n- **Grand Theft Auto: Chinatown Wars**\n\nHowever, **GTA IV remains unavailable** on Android platforms. The game was initially released in 2008 for consoles like PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360, as well as for Windows PC. While there have been ports and updates for newer platforms over the years, an official Android version has not been announced or released.\n\nIf you're interested in playing GTA IV, you would need to access it through supported platforms such as:\n\n- **PlayStation 3**\n- **Xbox 360**\n- **Windows PC**\n\nAlways ensure to download games from official sources to avoid potential security risks associated with unauthorized or pirated versions.\n\nIf Rockstar Games decides to release GTA IV or a version tailored for Android in the future, they will likely announce it through their official channels. Keep an eye on Rockstar's [official website](https://www.rockstargames.com/) or their social media profiles for the latest updates.",
